Hamas kini mendapat bantuan serangan dari pasukan Al Houthi dari Yaman. Pasukan tersebut telah mengirim rudal dan roket ke Israel pada Kamis (19/10). Perang Israel dan Hamas semakin meluas dengan adanya bantuan dari Al Houthi. Rudal dan roket yang dilancarkan pasukan itupun dilumpuhkan oleh kapal perang AS USS Carney. Meski tak ada korban jiwa, namun tembakan dari Yaman itu mengindikasikan bahwa Al Houthi sudah mulai turun tangan membantu Hamas. Diketahui sebelumnya, pemimpin Gerakan Ansarullah Sayyed Abdul Malik Badreddine Al Houthi sempat memberikan keterangannya. Pihaknya menegaskan bahwa Yaman siap untuk berpartisipasi dalam melancarkan serangan roket dan pesawat tak berawak. Hal itu dilakukan jika Amerika melakukan intervensi langsung dalam agresi Israel ke Gaza. Dalam pidatonya, Al Houthi menekankan bahwa rakyat Yaman siap melakukan segala yang mereka bisa untuk membela Palestina. Bahkan pasukan itu menyebut pembelaan terhadap Palestina adalah suatu tugas yang suci. Selain itu, ia juga menekankan bahwa Operasi badai Al Aqsa dari Hamas merupakan respons yang sah terhadap kekejaman Israel selama beberapa dekade terhadap warga Palestina. Sebelumnya sekutu Iran di Iraq dan Yaman mulai mengambil posisi setelah Amerika Serikat (AS) menegaskan komitmennya untuk membantu Israel. Today, the first convoy of humanitarian assistance since Hamasâ€™s October 7 terrorist attack on Israel crossed the border into Gaza and reached Palestinians in need. The opening of this essential supply route was the result of days of diplomatic engagement at the highest levels. I made it clear from the outset of this crisis--in both my public statements and private conversations--that humanitarian assistance was a critical and urgent need that had to get moving, and I express my deep personal appreciation for the leadership of President Al-Sisi of Egypt, Prime Minister Netanyahu of Israel, and the United Nations to allow the resumption of this assistance. The United States remains committed to ensuring that civilians in Gaza will continue to have access to food, water, medical care, and other assistance, without diversion by Hamas. We will continue to work with all parties to keep the Rafah crossing in operation to enable the continued movement of aid that is imperative to the welfare of the people of Gaza, and to continue working to protect civilians, consistent with obligations under international humanitarian law. We also continue to work around the clock, in partnership with Egypt and Israel, to facilitate the ability of U.S. citizens and their immediate family members to exit Gaza safely and travel via Egypt to their final destinations.

Serangan Bertubi-tubi Hizbullah Bikin Israel Evakuasi Warga ke Perbatasan Lebanon Militer Israel mengumumkan rencana untuk mengevakuasi penduduk di Kota Kiryat Shmona di wilayah utara yang berbatasan dengan Lebanon pada Jumat (20/10/2023). Rencana ini datang setelah Israel terus terlibat kontak senjata dengan para Hizbullah di sepanjang perbatasan dengan Lebanon. Beberapa saat yang lalu, Komando Utara telah menginformasikan kepada walikota kota tersebut mengenai keputusan itu. Hizbullah yang didukung Iran dan faksi-faksi Palestina yang bersekutu dengan Iran telah melakukan kontak senjata dengan Israel selama berhari-hari belakangan ini. Itu terjadi setelah kelompok Hamas menyerang komunitas di Israel selatan pada 7 Oktober dan dilaporkan menewaskan sedikitnya 1.400 orang. Sementara, lebih dari 3.700 warga Palestina, sebagian besar warga sipil, telah terbunuh di seluruh Jalur Gaza dalam pengeboman Israel, menurut angka dari kementerian kesehatan yang dikelola Hamas. Militer Israel mengatakan bahwa pasukannya terus menargetkan sasaran Hizbullah seiring dengan meningkatnya ketegangan di sepanjang perbatasan. IDF (Pasukan Pertahanan Israel) melakukan sejumlah serangan terhadap infrastruktur Hezbollah, termasuk pos-pos pengamatan. Selain itu, dikatakan, jet-jet tempur IDF menghantam tiga pasukan yang mencoba meluncurkan rudal anti-tank ke arah Israel. Pihak berwenang Israel tampak terus berupaya mengevakuasi masyarakat di seluruh perbatasan utara, ketika pasukan cadangan, kolom tank, dan kendaraan lapis baja mengalir ke daerah tersebut. editor : ica

Setelah tertunda akibat cuaca, rupanya Israel kini bersiap untuk melakukan serangan darat ke Gaza. Ratusan kendaraan lapis baja tersebut terlihat dalam citra satelit, berada sekira 6 km dari perbatasan utara Gaza. Hal ini menunjukkan kemungkinan bahwa Israel bergegas mengerahkan pasukan dalam jarak 10 kilometer dari perbatasan sebagai persiapan untuk invasi darat. Dilansir dari Nikkei.com, foto tersebut dianalisis dari gambar yang diambil oleh operator satelit yang berbasis di AS. Informasi tersebut disampaikan oleh Hidenori Watanabe, profesor studi informasi di Universitas Tokyo. â€œSekitar 200 kendaraan yang diduga milik Israel dikumpulkan. Kemungkinan besar militer Israel sedang mempersiapkan invasi darat,â€ kata Hidenori Watanabe, profesor studi informasi di Universitas Tokyo. Di sisi lain, foto kendaraan lapis baja yang diambil dari darat juga telah beredar. Dari foto tersebut, lokasinya berada sekira 1,5 km sebelah utara dari tempat kendaraan teridentifikasi. Saat memeriksa gambar yang diambil oleh Planet Labs di lokasi yang sama, terlihat lebih dari 200 objek mirip kendaraan. Semua itu diyakini merupakan kendaraan lapis baja Israel dan lainnya. Olives in Israel ğŸ‡®ğŸ‡± In ancient Jewish traditions, olives were significant for their use in religious rituals, such as lighting the Menorah and anointing ceremonies. They also symbolized prosperity, peace, and the deep connection to the land of Israel. In the New Testament, olives are symbolically associated with significant events and teachings related to Jesus. The Garden of Gethsemane, located among olive trees, is where Jesus prayed before his crucifixion. Olive trees are also used in parables to convey spiritual lessons. Anointing with oil is mentioned for healing and consecration, and the Mount of Olives serves as the backdrop for important events in Jesus' life, such as his Ascension. Hamas pada hari Jumat, 20 Oktober 2023, membebaskan seorang wanita Amerika Serikat (AS) dan putrinya yang masih remaja yang disandera di Gaza, menurut otoritas Israel. Ini merupakan pembebasan pertama dari sekitar 200 orang yang diculik kelompok militan tersebut dari Israel selama serangan mereka pada 7 Oktober. Speech by President Abdel Fattah El-Sisi President of the Arab Republic of Egypt At the Cairo Peace Summit â€œIn the Name of Allah, the Most Beneficent, the Most Mercifulâ€ Your Majesties, Highnesses and Excellences The Kings, Princes, Heads of State and Government Honorable Attendees We are meeting in Cairo today at a challenging time that tests our humanity before our interests and the depth of our faith in the value of the human being and in his right to life. The principles we profess to support are also called into question and scrutinized in these difficult times. I tell you honestly, that all the peoples of the world, not only the peoples of this region, are following with eyes wide open our stances at this momentous and historical moment, in the wake of the military escalation which began on the seventh of October in Israel and the Palestinian territories. Egypt condemns, in the clearest terms, the targeting, killing and intimidation of all peaceful civilians. At the same time, Egypt is expressing its deep shock that the world is standing by idly, while the catastrophic humanitarian crisis unfolds. Two and a half million Palestinians in the Gaza Strip are being subjected to collective punishment. They are living under siege and facing starvation and ferocious pressure of forced displacement, through practices condemned by the civilized world that has concluded agreements and established the international law and humanitarian international law to criminalize and prohibit their recurrence. This compels us to restate our call to provide international protection for the Palestinian people and the innocent civilians. And let me ask frankly: Where are the values of human civilization that we have established over long millennia and decades? Where is equality of human souls without discrimination or segregation or double standards? From the very first moment, Egypt has engaged in unyielding, strenuous and vigorous efforts, day and night, to coordinate and deliver humanitarian aid and relief to the besieged Palestinians in Gaza. Egypt has not closed the Rafah land crossing at any moment. However, the repeated Israeli shelling of the Palestinian side obstructed its operation. Amidst the severity of the circumstances on the ground, I agreed with the American President to operate the crossing on a sustainable basis, under the supervision of and coordination with the United Nations, the UNRWA and the Palestinian Red Crescent. The aid and relief shall be distributed under the supervision of the United Nations to the people in the Gaza Strip. Ladies and Gentlemen, The world must never condone the use of human suffering to force people into displacement. Egypt has affirmed, and is reiterating, its vehement rejection of the forced displacement of the Palestinians and their transfer to Egyptian lands in Sinai, as this will mark the last gasp in the liquidation of the Palestinian cause, shatter the dream of an independent Palestinian state, and squander the struggle of the Palestinian people and that of the Arab and Islamic peoples over the course of the Palestinian cause that has endured for 75 years. He will be mistaken in his understanding of the nature of the Palestinian people, whoever thinks that these proud, steadfast and resilient people are willing to abandon their land, even if that land is under occupation or bombardment. I want to state it clearly and unequivocally to the world, and articulate in sincere terms the will of all the Egyptian people, every single Egyptian: that the liquidation of the Palestinian cause without a just solution is beyond the realm of possibility, and in all cases it will never happen at the expense of Egypt, absolutely not. Honorable Attendees, Is this region destined to endure this conflict for eternity? Isnâ€™t it about time to address the root causes of the problem of the Middle East. Hasnâ€™t the time come yet to dispel the political illusions that the status quo can sustain, meaning the state of unilateral measures, settlements, the desecration of holy sites, and uprooting of the Palestinians from their homes and villages and from Al Quds Al Sharif (The Holy City of Jerusalem). Egypt has paid a heavy price for peace to prevail in this region .. it initiated it when the voice of war predominated .. and maintained it alone .. when the voice of hollow exaggerations was prevalent. Egypt stood tall, leading its region toward peaceful co-existence based on justice. Today, Egypt is telling you in all candor and sincerity: that the solution for the Palestinian cause is not displacement, and is not by forcibly transferring the entire people to other regions; the one and only solution is justice, with the Palestinians obtaining their legitimate rights for self-determination, and leading a proud and safe life in an independent state on their land like the rest of the peoples of the earth Ladies and Gentlemen, We are encountering an unprecedented crisis, that necessitates utmost (truncated)

Ribuan umat muslim dari berbagai organisasi Islam dan perorangan turun ke jalan, melakukan aksi bela Palestina, Sabtu 21 Oktober 2023. Aksi bela Palestina ini diinisiasi oleh oleh Aliansi Masyarakat Jawa Barat Peduli Palestina (AMJP2). Aksi itu dimulai dengan kumpul di Masjid Pusdai, Jalan Diponegoro, Kota Bandung. Ribuan massa itu kemudian bergeser ke Gedung Sate dan melakukan orasi di sana. Orasi dilakukan secara bergantian dari perwakilan setiap ormas Islam dan tokoh Jawa Barat seperti Persis, Muhammadiyah, PUI, Al Irsyad, Ikadi dan Salimah Jabar. Sedangkan dari tokoh Jabar ada mantan Gubernur Jawa Barat, Ahmad Heryawan, dan Ust Athian Ali. Setelah orasi, masa kemudian melakukan longmarch sambil membentangkan bendera Palestina berukuran raksasa. October 22, 2023 Twenty-ninth Sunday in Ordinary Time Lectionary: 145 Reading 1 Is 45:1, 4-6 Thus says the LORD to his anointed, Cyrus, whose right hand I grasp, subduing nations before him, and making kings run in his service, opening doors before him and leaving the gates unbarred: For the sake of Jacob, my servant, of Israel, my chosen one, I have called you by your name, giving you a title, though you knew me not. I am the LORD and there is no other, there is no God besides me. It is I who arm you, though you know me not, so that toward the rising and the setting of the sun people may know that there is none besides me. I am the LORD, there is no other. The Word of the Lord Thanks be to God Responsorial Psalm Ps 96:1, 3, 4-5, 7-8, 9-10 R. (7b) Give the Lord glory and honor. Sing to the LORD a new song; sing to the LORD, all you lands. Tell his glory among the nations; among all peoples, his wondrous deeds. R. Give the Lord glory and honor. For great is the LORD and highly to be praised; awesome is he, beyond all gods. For all the gods of the nations are things of nought, but the LORD made the heavens. R. Give the Lord glory and honor. Give to the LORD, you families of nations, give to the LORD glory and praise; give to the LORD the glory due his name! Bring gifts, and enter his courts. R. Give the Lord glory and honor. Worship the LORD, in holy attire; tremble before him, all the earth; say among the nations: The LORD is king, he governs the peoples with equity. R. Give the Lord glory and honor. Reading 2 1 Thes 1:1-5b Paul, Silvanus, and Timothy to the church of the Thessalonians in God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ: grace to you and peace. We give thanks to God always for all of you, remembering you in our prayers, unceasingly calling to mind your work of faith and labor of love and endurance in hope of our Lord Jesus Christ, before our God and Father, knowing, brothers and sisters loved by God, how you were chosen. For our gospel did not come to you in word alone, but also in power and in the Holy Spirit and with much conviction. The Word of the Lord Thanks be to God Alleluia Phil 2:15d, 16a R. Alleluia, alleluia. Shine like lights in the world as you hold on to the word of life. R. Alleluia, alleluia. Gospel Mt 22:15-21 The Pharisees went off and plotted how they might entrap Jesus in speech. They sent their disciples to him, with the Herodians, saying, "Teacher, we know that you are a truthful man and that you teach the way of God in accordance with the truth. And you are not concerned with anyone's opinion, for you do not regard a person's status. Tell us, then, what is your opinion: Is it lawful to pay the census tax to Caesar or not?" Knowing their malice, Jesus said, "Why are you testing me, you hypocrites? Show me the coin that pays the census tax." Then they handed him the Roman coin. He said to them, "Whose image is this and whose inscription?" They replied, "Caesar's." At that he said to them, "Then repay to Caesar what belongs to Caesar and to God what belongs to God." Over 300,000 people gathered in central London on Saturday to protest against Israel's continued bombardment on Gaza.

The "from the river to the sea, Palestine will be free" chant was being echoed by thousands who amassed near Downing Street as more people were still joining the march, according to the Palestine Solidarity Campaign (PSC).

London's Metropolitan Police on Friday said they will not be arresting anyone chanting the popular slogan "from the river to the sea".

The chant is commonly heard at solidarity marches and refers to the area of historic Palestine between the River Tiberias and the Mediterranean Sea.

Pro-Israel groups claim it is antisemitic because it is an implicit call for the destruction of Israel, a charge rejected by Palestinian activists.

Presiden Otoritas Palestina, Mahmoud Abbas, yang juga politisi Partai Fatah, mengatakan tindakan dan kebijakan kelompok Hamas tidak mewakili rakyat Palestina, menurut kantor berita resmi WAFA, Minggu (15/10).â£
â£
Lalu siapa Hamas, dan apa bedanya dengan Fatah?â£
â£
Hamas dan Fatah adalah dua partai paling dominan di kancah politik Palestina. â£
â£
Serangan mematikan Hamas di selatan Israel pada 7 Oktober lalu, merupakan bukti berkembangnya keahlian militer mereka sejak mengambil alih Gaza pada 2007. â£
â£
Dilansir Reuters, Hamas kini memiliki akademi militer yang melatih berbagai spesialisasi termasuk keamanan siber.â£
â£
Sejak awal 2000-an, Hamas juga membangun jaringan terowongan bawah tanah di Gaza untuk membantu pasukannya melarikan diri, mendirikan pabrik senjata, dan mendatangkan senjata dari luar negeri.â£
â£
Hamas adalah bagian dari aliansi regional yang terdiri dari Iran, Suriah, dan kelompok Islam Syiah Hizbullah di Lebanon. Semuanya menentang kebijakan AS di Timur Tengah.â£
â£
Fatah lebih memilih jalur negosiasi untuk memerdekakan Palestina.â£
â£
Di bawah pendirinya, Yasser Arafat, dan setelah Perang Arab-Israel tahun 1967, Fatah menjadi partai dominan di Organisasi Pembebasan Palestina (PLO). Saat ini, PLO bertindak sebagai perwakilan rakyat Palestina di PBB.â£
â£
Pada 1993, Arafat mewakili Otoritas Palestina menandatangani perjanjian damai dengan Israel untuk mengelola Gaza dan Tepi Barat yang diduduki Israel. Saat itu terjadi demonstrasi besar dari warga Palestina yang tidak menyetujui perjanjian ini.â£

McDonald's Indonesia Buka Suara soal  Seruan Boikot

 PT Rekso Nasional Food, pemegang lisensi McDonald's di Indonesia buka suara terkait kontroversi aksi McDonald's memberi makanan gratis kepada tentara dan warga Israel. Pemberian makanan itu dilakukan di tengah memanasnya konflik antara Israel dan Hamas di Jalur Gaza.

Associate Director of Communications McDonald's Indonesia Meta Rostiawati mengatakan bersimpati kepada para korban, keluarga, dan komunitas yang terdampak. Dia juga merasa prihatin melihat memanasnya konflik yang terjadi di Timur Tengah.

"PT Rekso Nasional Food sangat prihatin melihat eskalasi konflik baru-baru ini di Timur Tengah. Sebagai pemegang waralaba yang memiliki peran dalam mengembangkan jaringan McDonald's di Indonesia, bagi kami komunitas adalah jantung dari bisnis perusahaan," ujar Meta dalam keterangan tertulis, Sabtu (21/10/2023).

Meta juga menegaskan PT Rekso Nasional Food, perusahaan swasta nasional yang sepenuhnya dimiliki oleh pengusaha asli Indonesia. McDonald's Indonesia beroperasi secara independen dan tidak terhubung dengan kegiatan operasional maupun keputusan McDonald's negara lain, termasuk McDonald's Israel.

Dia bilang, McDonald's Indonesia akan terus memberikan pelayanan terbaik bagi pelanggan, menyajikan makanan dengan kualitas terdepan dan memberikan manfaat yang besar bagi sekitar dan masyarakat Indonesia.

"Terkait dengan pemberitaan terakhir mengenai McDonald's, kami ingin menegaskan bahwa PT Rekso Nasional Food adalah perusahaan swasta nasional, yang sepenuhnya dimiliki oleh pengusaha asli Indonesia dengan jumlah karyawan lebih dari 16.000 tenaga kerja lokal. McDonald's Indonesia merupakan entitas yang beroperasi secara independen dan tidak terafiliasi dengan kegiatan operasional maupun keputusan McDonald's di negara lain, termasuk McDonald's Israel," tegasnya

Perusahaan dengan jumlah karyawan lebih dari 16.000 tenaga kerja lokal tersebut akan terus berupaya menjadi bagian yang positif dari komunitas di tempatnya beroperasi. Selain itu, difokuskan untuk memberikan pengalaman McDonald's yang disukai dan dipercaya pelanggan.

On 17 October, an explosion ripped through the car park of Al-Ahli Hospital in northern Gaza, killing at least 500 Palestinians, many of whom were sheltering or being treated there. Preliminary analysis by FA, @al_haq_organization, and @earshot.ngo casts doubt on IOF claims that the source of the blast was a misfired Palestinian rocket travelling west to east. 

(1) 

As seen in slide 1, 3D analysis of the impact crater shows patterns of radial fragmentation on its SW side and a shallow channel leading into it from the NE. Such patterns indicate a likely projectile trajectory with northeast origins, the direction of the Israeli-controlled side of the Gaza perimeter. 

Analysis from explosive weapons expert @cobbsmith supports this initial reading. We cannot yet make a definitive assessment regarding the munition type, but our/@cobbsmithâ€™s assessment of the crater suggests it is more consistent with the impact marks from an artillery shell than typical IOF missiles.

(2) 

Using available footage, @earshot.ngo performed audio analysis of the strike, which contributes further to our understanding of directionality. Slide 2 shows their Doppler Effect analysis of one of the videos, which indicates that the missile was closer to the camera before hitting the hospital and so had approached the hospital from NE, E, or SE, rather than SW. 

(3) 

Israel has falsely claimed that â€˜the IDF does not hit hospitalsâ€™. Yet @al_haq_organization has footage of an IOF strike on the Al-Ahli Hospital cancer ward on 14 Oct just 3 days prior, and WHO has reported 59 attacks on healthcare in Gaza since 7 Oct alone.

@earshot_ngo analysed the recording released by IOF officials of an alleged intercepted call between Hamas members implicating the Islamic Jihad in the attack. In slide 3, they show that the voices are divided across 2 separate channels, meaning they were recorded independently and then edited together with added effects. As the recording was manipulated, they find it is not a credible source of evidence. 

A conclusive investigation into this attack will require full access to the site and munition fragments, as well as witness interviews. Our work on this case is ongoing.

A letter written by Albert Einstein in 1948, less than 24 hours after news filtered through about the Deir Yassin massacre in Jerusalem in April 1948. Around 120 settler terrorists from Menachem Beginâ€™s Irgun and the Stern militia (headed by another terrorist who went on to become prime minister of Israel, Yitzhak Shamir), entered the Palestinian village and slaughtered between nearly 250 men, women and children. Some died from gunshots, others from hand grenades thrown into their homes. Others living in the peaceful village were killed after being taken on a grotesque parade through West Jerusalem. There were also reports of rape, torture and mutilation.

A month later the British ended their Mandate rule in Palestine and Israel came into being. The legitimacy claimed by its founders was the November 1947 UN Partition Resolution which proposed that Palestine be divided into two states, one Jewish and one Arab, with Jerusalem administered independently of either side.

Although Einstein was an early supporter of the idea of Zionism, by the late 1930s he had turned away from the ideology, rejecting and critiquing it in several letters and talks. It was the violence in the run up to the birth of Israel that particularly revulsed Einstein, and no doubt this was foremost in his mind when he turned down the offer to become Israelâ€™s president. This offer was put to him in 1952 by the stateâ€™s founding Prime Minister, David Ben-Gurion.

Ten years before the state declared its â€œindependenceâ€ in 1948 on land stolen from the people of Palestine, Einstein described the proposed creation of Israel as something which conflicted with â€œthe essential nature of Judaism.â€

In 1948, he and a number of Jewish academics also sent a letter to the New York Times to protest against a visit to America by Menachem Begin. In the well-documented letter, they denounced Beginâ€™s Herut (Freedom) party, likening it to â€œa political party closely akin in its organisation, methods, political philosophy and social appeal to the Nazi and Fascist parties.â€ Herut was a right-wing nationalist party which went on to become the Likud led by Benjamin Netanyahu.

â€œItâ€™s pitch black, and I hear nothing but low-flying jet fighters raining missiles nearby. Among my jumbled thoughts are the friends and relatives Iâ€™ve lost - at least nine so far - and whether Iâ€™ll make it through the night alive.

Living in the besieged Gaza Strip for 27 years and surviving five Israeli attacks on Gaza has taught me what to do in times of war.

Itâ€™s a pattern that keeps repeating itself. After the first bomb explodes, we rush to the nearest supermarket to stock up on high-carb foods, which can help us stay strong for a longer time. We bid farewell to loved ones, knowing our lives depend on the trajectory of the next missile.

In the case of a quick evacuation, we put important documents and cash in an emergency bag, leaving our most cherished memories at home. We crowd together in our main room so that if the house were bombed, we could all be found together.

The most important lesson is to never trust the night, which is when Israel commits its most horrific atrocities.

No one believes they will survive the war at this point. We have seen dozens of Israeli air strikes in Deir Balah, Khan Younis, Rafah and other areas in the south, where Israel told the population to relocate. Israel wants to convince us that we will never be safe.

We are guilty of having hoped, and for a moment even believed, that we deserved a good life, a quiet life - or at least a normal life without constant bombs, fear and loss.

The days pass with the agony of not knowing the latest news, because we have no electricity or internet connection. This agony intensifies in the brief moments when the signal returns; my heart pounds rapidly in my chest, for fear of new messages that we donâ€™t want to read.â€

Ribuan umat Islam di Jawa Barat menggelar aksi solidaritas untuk Palestina di kawasan Gedung Sate, Kota Bandung. Aksi ini diikuti oleh puluhan komunitas, ormas, elemen dan lembaga Islam di Jawa Barat.
Aksi bertajuk AKSI JAWA BARAT DUKUNG PALESTINA ini akan diikuti juga oleh sejumlah tokoh seperti Ahmad Heryawan (Gubernur Jabar 2008-2018), KH. Zaitun Rasmin (Ketua Wahdah Islamiyah Pusat), KH. Athian Ali (Ketua FUUI), KH. Abdul Qohar Al Qodsy (Ketua DTN PA 212), Al-Ustadz Muhammad Roinul (Ketua Dewan Dakwah Jabar), Al-Ustadz Ardiansyah Ashri Husein (Ketua KNRP Jabar), Al-Ustadz Mulyadi (Daarut Tauhid), Al-Ustadz Iman Budiman (ketua DPW PUI Jabar), Al-Ustadz Amin Buchaery (ketua Jundullah ANNAS), Al-Ustadz Roni Abdul Fattah (Pengasuh Ponpes Darul Iman), Muzammil Hasballah (Qorie/influencer) dan masih banyak lagi.

Longmarch para peserta aksi akan dilakukan dari Gedung Sate menuju Gedung Merdeka di Jalan Asia Afrika. Pantauan detikJabar, Sabtu (21/10/2023) sekitar Pukul 07.45 WIB, ribuan massa aksi datang dari arah Pusdai dengan berjalan kaki menuju ke Kawasan Gedung Sate.

"Palestina, Palestina, bebaskan, bebaskan. Israel, Israel, hancurkan, hancurkan," teriak massa aksi.

Arul Dimas demonstran asal Cimahi mengatakan, dia mengikuti aksi tersebut sebagai bentuk solideritas Palestina.

"Semoga banyak yang berpartisipasi yang membela Palestina. Israel sudah keterlaluan," kata Arul kepada detikJabar.

Arul mengaku sedih, pasalnya saat ini korban kekejaman Israel kebanyakan wanita dan anak-anak.

"Banyak juga rumah sakit dan gedung sekolah dihancurkan," tambah Arul.

Arul berharap kepada pemerintah Indonesia agar membantu perjuangan rakyat Palestina, salah satunya dengan mengirim bantuan tentara ke Palestina.

"Semoga ada relawan atau tentara yang dikirim kesana," pungkasnya.

Winnie Madikizela-Mandela (born Nomzamo Winifred Zanyiwe Madikizela; September 26, 1936 - April 2, 2018), also known as Winnie Mandela, was a South African anti-apartheid activist and politician, and the second wife of Nelson Mandela. She served as a Member of Parliament from 1994 to 2003, and from 2009 until her death, and was a deputy minister of arts and culture from 1994 to 1996

A member of the African National Congress (ANC) political party, she served on the ANC's National Executive Committee and headed its Women's League. Madikizela-Mandela was known to her supporters as the "Mother of the Nation".

While many people focus on Nelson Mandelaâ€™s solidarity with Palestine, many overlook Winnie Mandelaâ€™s political commitments to Palestine as well.

â€œThis comment came as she addressed a meeting arranged by a Palestinian solidarity organization in Lenasia, Johannesburg, and she was known to be a staunch supporter of the Boycott, Divestment and Sanctions movement.â€

Ratusan mahasiswa Universitas Syiah Kuala dan berbagai elemen masyarakat Aceh menggelar aksi bersatu membela Palestina di Bundaran Simpang Lima, Kota Banda Aceh, Sabtu (21/10/2023). 

Massa yang tergabung dalam berbagai organisasi memenuhi Tugu Simpang Lima.

Massa terlihat membawa berbagai atribut seperti bendera Palestina, ikat kepala bertuliskan "Save Palestine", spanduk berisikan tulisan "Aceh Bela Palestina" dan mobil pick up yang membawa pengeras suara. 

Sebelum memulai aksi, seorang peserta aksi mengumandangkan adzan dari pengeras suara di hadapan para peserta aksi lainnya di Tugu Simpang Lima. 

"Perampasan tanah Palestina sudah berlangsung dari ratusan tahun lalu, saudara kita hanya mencoba memperjuangkan tanah mereka," kata Koordinator Lapangan, Dedi Muhardi. 

Selama orasi massa juga meneriakkan embel-embel "Allahu Akbar" dengan antusias. Massa juga berkali-kali meneriakkan kemerdekaan untuk Palestina.

Massa juga menyebarkan beberapa lembaran kertas yang bergambar bendera Israel dan bendera Amerika di jalanan sekitar Bundaran Simpang Lima.

Kertas-kertas yang memuat gambar bendera Amerika dan Israel dibiarkan terlindas oleh kendaraan-kendaraan yang lewat. 

Selain berorasi, seorang peserta aksi juga membacakan puisi tentang duka yang dialami oleh Palestina. Di akhir aksi, massa ikut membakar bendera Israel dan Amerika Serikat.

Did you know that in 2016, many U.S. states passed laws that can punish you for boycotting Israel? These laws are called anti-BDS laws, and they are meant to protect Israel from boycotts. But some people think these laws are unfair and against the right to free speech. They have taken these laws to court and some judges have agreed with them. Other people think these laws are good and necessary to support Israel and fight antisemitism. They say these laws do not stop people from speaking, but only affect how they do business or spend money. There are also some people who want to make new rules at the national level that would support or enforce these state rules, or say that boycotting Israel is bad. But these rules have not become U.S. law yet. There are also some people who want to make new rules that would support a peaceful solution for the conflict between Israel and Palestinians, and say that Israel should stop occupying their land. But these rules have faced a lot of opposition from people who support Israel.

What do you think about these laws and the issues behind them? Share your thoughts in the comments below. #FreePalestine #AntiBDS #IsraelPalestine

Gazaâ€™s Hamas rulers released two Americans on Friday among some 200 hostages they abducted in October 7 attacks in Israel and indicated that more could follow.

Judith Tai Raanan, 59, and her daughter Natalie, 17, were handed over to Israeli forces at the Gaza Strip border on Friday, becoming the first captives whose release by Hamas has been confirmed by both sides since the latest round of Arab-Israeli bloodshed erupted.\

The release was announced by Abu Ubaida, a spokesman of Hamas, the Izz el-Deen al-Qassam Brigades, and confirmed a short time later in a statement from Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.

Kecam Israel, Ricky Smartphone Galang Dana Mandiri untuk Palestina 

Pemilik @rickysmartphone.id H.Ricky Hartono Putra mengecam perbuatan Israel terhadap Palestina, "ini bukan lagi tentang agama tapi ini kemanusiaan ,mari kita bersama2 berdoa supaya saudara2 kita di Palestina segera diberikan kebebasan, setiap hari mereka dihantui rasa takut bom, tembakan, rumah sakit pun di bom, jiwa2 yg tidak bersalah melayang begitu saja" ungkap H.Ricky, Jumat (20/10).

Karena itu, Ia mengajak warga NTB untuk memberi dukungan baik moril maupun materiil, "Saya mengajak seluruh masyarakat NTB ikut serta setidaknya dengan bantu doa, kalo tidak bisa harta dan jiwa membantu, semoga invasi serangan Israel dan sekutu ke Palestina segera bisa berakhir" harapnya. 

Ia menambahkan, untuk masyarakat NTB khususnya siapapun yg ingin berdonasi harus tau betul validitas lembaga yg ingin diberikan amanah, jangan sampai disalahgunakan untuk kepentingan pribadi. 

Berkaitan dengan itu, Ricky Smartphone berkomitmen mulai hari ini (Jumat, 20/10) akan menyisihkan sebagian keuntungan penjualan handphonoe untuk donasi ke Palestina, "Setiap yang membeli hp di @rickysmartphone dari tgl 21-31 oktober 2023 maka ia telah ikut serta berdonasi untuk palestina" terang H.Ricky. 

"Hasil donasi akan kami umumkan secara terbuka, bagi masyarakat yg ingin berdonasi juga kami persilahkan melalui yayasan rickyhartono Foundation dengan wa ke nomer 08174772519" ungkap H. Ricky.

"Sebelumnya kami ucapkan terimakasih, sekali lagi mari kita doakan saudara2 kita di palestina agak penderitaannya segera berakhir" pungkasnya.

Ribuan umat Islam di Jawa Barat menggelar aksi solidaritas untuk Palestina di kawasan Gedung Sate, Kota Bandung. Aksi ini diikuti oleh puluhan komunitas, ormas, elemen dan lembaga Islam di Jawa Barat.

Longmarch para peserta aksi akan dilakukan dari Gedung Sate menuju Gedung Merdeka di Jalan Asia Afrika. Pantauan detikJabar, Sabtu (21/10/2023) sekitar Pukul 07.45 WIB, ribuan massa aksi datang dari arah Pusdai dengan berjalan kaki menuju ke Kawasan Gedung Sate.

"Palestina, Palestina, bebaskan, bebaskan. Israel, Israel, hancurkan, hancurkan," teriak massa aksi.

Arul Dimas demonstran asal Cimahi mengatakan, dia mengikuti aksi tersebut sebagai bentuk solideritas Palestina.

"Semoga banyak yang berpartisipasi yang membela Palestina. Israel sudah keterlaluan," kata Arul kepada detikJabar.

Arul mengaku sedih, pasalnya saat ini korban kekejaman Israel kebanyakan wanita dan anak-anak.

"Banyak juga rumah sakit dan gedung sekolah dihancurkan," tambah Arul.

Arul berharap kepada pemerintah Indonesia agar membantu perjuangan rakyat Palestina, salah satunya dengan mengirim bantuan tentara ke Palestina.

"Semoga ada relawan atau tentara yang dikirim kesana," pungkasnya.

The reactions across the globe have ranged widely and almost every country has expressed solidarity with either Israel or Palestine â€” who, as a result of the violence, have allies and enemies. A report by Reuters delves into recent arrests of Arab citizens in Israel due to their social media posts expressing solidarity with Palestinians in Gaza. â 
â 
In one case, Palestinian singer and neuroscientist Dalal Abu Amneh filed a complaint with Israeli police after receiving death threats in response to her social media post. The post featured a Palestinian flag emoji and the words "There is no victor but God." According to Reuters, Israeli authorities accused her of promoting hate speech and incitement to her nearly 300,000 followers. She was detained for two days, placed under house arrest, and prohibited from discussing the conflict for 45 days.â 
â 
In another case, a 60-year-old urban planner faced arrest for posting a sketch and analysis of potential Israeli ground invasion scenarios into Gaza. According to Reuters, ground Invasion scenarios are discussed regularly in Israeli media.â 
â 
Israel has established a specialized task force focused on tracking and combating online incitement to terrorism. Police spokesperson Eli Levy revealed that this special team, formed in February, had spotted nearly 180 posts since October 7th. â 
â 
Levy said that out of the 96 individuals under investigation, 63 of them had already been detained, "in some cases, within 40 minutes of the publication of a post".â 
â

Amplifying @savethechildrenâ€™s and the UNâ€™s message and adding a few thoughts. Itâ€™s hard not to express the sheer helplessness and sorrow many of us are experiencing right now.  So much has been said. So much more can be said. And whatever anyone says today, is always going to upset someone or the other simply because perspective is very personal for each individual. But there are some feelings we all share. At least I believe that. We all share a love for peace. For a decent life. We share the right to safety and freedom. And we share a common bond of empathy when others in our tribe are being harmed. 

The fact is we are all collectively grieving right now. For the people of Gaza who are in an unimaginable situation and donâ€™t seem to have any recourse to safety. Their plight gets worse by the minute. People have lost everything. This needs to stop. 
We feel for the families of citizens of Israel who were killed and the hostages that are still being held and whose fate is unknown. 
The fact is all people have one thing in common. They belong to the human race. And through no individual fault of theirs they are now suffering terribly. 

Donâ€™t tell me this conflict cannot be stopped by Israel using more peaceful methods. I refuse to believe that. If there was a collective will to stop this, with the help of all the other nations trying so desperately to prevent further escalation - it is possible. 

A country doesnâ€™t become weaker by ending a war or an invasion or an aggression. In fact itâ€™s the opposite. Ditto for Hamas. Any desire to wipe out anyone else is never going to work. Humanity over politics is the only way out. 

There just needs to be a willingness to do so.

Umat menghadiri pemakaman di Gereja Ortodoks Yunani Saint Porphyrius, di Kota Gaza.

Serangan udara terhadap gedung yang berdekatan dengan Gereja Ortodoks Yunani St. Porphyrios telah menewaskan beberapa orang yang berlindung di sana, dan mendapat kecaman keras dari Gereja-Gereja Kristen.

Bangunan tersebutâ€”yang berafiliasi dengan gereja tersebut, yang merupakan salah satu gereja tertua di Gazaâ€”runtuh akibat ledakan yang disebabkan oleh serangan rudal Israel, menurut Patriarkat Ortodoks Yunani.

Setidaknya 16 umat Kristiani, termasuk 10 dari satu keluarga, tewas pada Kamis malam dalam serangan udara di salah satu bangunan di kompleks Gereja Ortodoks Yunani St. Porphyrios di Gaza.  Beberapa orang lainnya dilaporkan masih terjebak di bawah puing-puing.

Sekitar 400 orang, sebagian besar beragama Kristen, berlindung di kompleks tersebut ketika perang dimulai hampir dua minggu lalu.

Patriarkat melaporkan bahwa sejumlah besar orang terluka akibat ledakan tersebutâ€”beberapa di antaranya seriusâ€”di antara pengungsi keluarga Kristen dan Muslim yang berlindung di gereja yang berdekatan dengan bangunan yang hancur yang tidak terkena dampak langsung.

Bangunan itu terletak beberapa ratus meter dari Gereja Katolik Keluarga Kudus, tempat 500 umat Kristiani berlindung.

Banyak keluarga dari kompleks Ortodoks Yunani harus pindah ke gereja paroki Keluarga Kudus, yang sudah terisi penuh.  Menurut sumber ACN (According to Aid to the Church in Need), kompleks Katolik juga dihantam bom kejut pada Kamis malam.

Now the hospital stands decimated, the site of carnage following Israel's bombing that killed at least 500 people Tuesday night, its memories and stories perishing. â€œThe hospital was a community,â€ Farah told Al Jazeera.â

.â

.â 
Farah's grandparents have passed away, but their memories continue to shape his Palestinian identity.â

The Archbishop recalled that the Pope  called on all Christians to pray and fast for peace on Friday, October 27, 2023.

â€œHe also encouraged people of other Christian denominations, other religions and all those who advocate for peace to participate as they see fit. The Pope

announced that the central event on Friday would be an hour of prayer at 6 pm in St. Peterâ€™s Square, with the goal of invoking peace for the world,â€ Fr Ferrao said.

The Archbishop said that in response to our beloved Holy Fatherâ€™s invitation, let us rise together and join him in observing coming Friday, the 27th of October, as a day of prayer, penance and fasting for peace in Israel and Palestine and between other war-torn countries and peoples.

â€œPrayer and penance can play a vital role in this endeavour. While we encourage individuals and families to join in this global spiritual exercise, we urge our Parish Priests, Chaplains, Heads of Institutions and of Religious Communities to organize for the people under their care at least an hour of prayer for this intention,â€ Fr Ferrao said.

Bazaar of Jerusalem, Ottoman Palestine, the early 1900s

Ottoman Jerusalem had three khans and several bazaars. The khans were the main wholesale markets for traders. Al-Wad street, which extends southward from Damascus Gate, is one of the main markets that still exists today.

The pricing of the goods took place in the presence of a group of merchants, the sheikh of the trades, and the muhtasib (inspector)- one of the chief assistants of the qadi, the judge. He supervised prices and weights, fixed prices of goods, combat fraud, and kept the roads open.

Famous Ottoman explorer Evliya Ã‡elebi visited Jerusalem around the year 1670 AD and recorded 2,045 shops in the city. Most of the shops were waqf property or endowments and, as such, were leased to the merchants, and the proceeds went towards charity funds, such as funds for sabils, schools, mosques, and Sufi zawiyahs.

TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM - Faksi poros perlawanan bersenjata di Yaman, Irak, Suriah, dan Lebanon melakukan operasi pada Kamis (19/10/2023).

Hal itu mereka lakukan untuk mendukung Hamas dan pejuang perlawanan Palestina dalam peperangan melawan Israel.

Dari Yaman, gerakan perlawanan Ansarallah menembakkan tiga rudal ke utara ke arah Israel.

Namun, kemudian berhasil dicegat oleh kapal perang Angkatan Laut milik Amerika Serikat (AS).

Dilansir Tribunnews.com, menurut para pejabat AS, kapal perusak Angkatan Laut di Laut Merah, yakni USS Carney berhasil mencegat serangan rudal-rudal dari Yaman tersebut.

"USS Carney, kapal perusak Angkatan Laut di Laut Merah, mencegat ketiga rudal tersebut," menurut para pejabat AS.

Gerakan Ansarallah sendiri telah melawan koalisi internasional pimpinan Arab Saudi sejak tahun 2015.

Pihaknya menyatakan dukungan terhadap Palestina dan mengancam Israel.

Pekan lalu, pemimpin Ansarallah, Abdel-Malek al-Houthi memperingatkan AS agar tidak ikut campur dalam konflik antara Israel dan Hamas.

Ia juga mengancam bahwa pasukannya akan membalas dengan menembakkan drone dan rudal.

Aksi pembelaan kepada Hamas selanjutnya adalah peristiwa rentetan rudal menyerang pangkalan Militer AS di Irak.

Pada Kamis (19/10) lalu, rudal Grad menargetkan pangkalan udara AS di Ain al-Asad di provinsi Anbar, Irak barat.

Informasi tersebut dikonfirmasi oleh sumber keamanan yang berbicara dengan Shafaq News.

"Pangkalan itu dihantam rentetan rudal," kata sumber itu kepada Kantor Berita Shafaq.

Meski begitu, AS mengklaim bahwa pihaknya dapat menghalau serangan rudal tersebut.

Adapun, selanjutnya, milisi perlawanan di Irak, yang terdiri dari faksi bersenjata Syiah, mengaku bertanggung jawab atas serangan terhadap pangkalan militer AS di Al-Tanf, Suriah.

Pangkalan tersebut, terletak di perbatasan Suriah, Yordania, dan Irak.

Serangan selanjutnya, adanya tiga drone berisi bahan peledak menghantam pangkalan militer AS di ladang gas Conoco.

Pangkalan itu terletak di provinsi timur Deir Ezzor yang berbatasan dengan Irak.

Rami Abdurrahman dari Observatorium Suriah untuk Hak Asasi Manusia yang berbasis di Inggris, sebuah lembaga pemantau perang, membenarkan bahwa terdengar kali ledakan di ladang gas Conoco tersebut.

Di sisi lain selain AS, Pos Militer Israel di Lebanon juga terkena serangan rudal

Pada hari yang sama, Kamis (19/10) lalu, sebuah peluru kendali diluncurkan dari Lebanon selatan.

Serangan itu, menargetkan pos terdepan militer Israel di pemukiman Menara alias Manara.

(Tribun-Video.com/Tribunnews.com)

TRIBUN-TIMUR.COM - Inilah rekaman detik-detik bom Israel berjatuhan di wilayah Gaza. 

Ledakan dahsyat hingga kepulan asap yang membumbung tinggi terekam jelas.

Videonya kemudian ramai beredar di Telegram pada Jumat, 20 Oktober 2023. 

Dalam keterangan unggahan disebutkan inilah Pengeboman Israel yang kejam di Gaza.

Lebih dari 1 juta warga Palestina mengungsi ke wilayah Selatan Gaza, setelah serangan udara Israel menghantam sejumlah lokasi di Jalur Gaza.

Termasuk di Deir Al Balah di Gaza Tengah, sebuah bangunan masjid hancur dihantam rudal Israel.

Serangan Israel paling mematikan terjadi di Rumah Sakit Al Ahli yang menewaskan lebih dari 500 orang termasuk pengungsi, pasien, dokter, dan perawat.

Serangan Israel ini dikecam sejumlah negara, termasuk Indonesia.

TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM - Pasukan Hamas terus menghujani roket ke wilayah selatan dan angkatan udara Israel.

Serangan pada Jumat (20/10) malam itu sampai membuat sistem pertahanan udara Israel Iron Dome kewalahan.

Bahkan Iron Dome pun sampi jebol dan menghantam Kota Ashkelon.

Pihak berwenang mengatakan bahwa roket yang diluncurkan dari Jalur Gaza itu membuat kota pesisir selatan Askhelon mengalami kerusakan.

Satu roket langsung menghantam sebuah rumah, menyebabkan kerusakan dan satu lagi menghantam sejumlah mobil.

Hal itu diungkapkan oleh Dinas Pemadam Kebakaran dan Penyelematan.
